==English==

===Etymology===
Italian ''Bergamasco'' (from Bergamo, itself from German ''Bergheim'', meaning "mountain home")

===Adjective===
'''Bergamask''', '''Bergomask'''

# Of or characteristic of Bergamo, Italy.

===Quotations===

'''1594-6''' Will it please you to see the epilogue, or to hear a Bergomask dance between two of our company? &mdash; Shakespeare, ''A Midsummer Night's Dream''